FBIS4-15594 "drsov069_s_94012" FBIS-SOV-94-069 Daily Report 9 Apr 1994 Georgia Explosion on Passenger Train Kills 3 Explosion on Passenger Train Kills 3 LD0904081094 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 0600 GMT 9 Apr 94 LD0904081094 Moscow Radio Rossii Network Russian BFN [Text] There was a powerful explosion at approximately 0400 hours today, 9 April, at Sadakhlo station in Marneuli, eastern Georgia, in one of the cars of a passenger train travelling from Tbilisi to Yerevan. Our correspondent Nikolay Mamulashvili has reported that according to preliminary figures, as a result of the blast three people were killed, a child was seriously injured, and three cars were burned out. Representatives of the Georgian Interior Ministry and special services have left for the scene of the incident.
